{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"3ad5128efb266e03a308e528192734081610fc68419c9eb39457e03cf590fdeb","created_at":"2026-03-03T07:56:40Z","created_by":"ordis","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Current GH_TOKEN is a classic PAT which grants write access to any repo the owner controls, including the upstream beadhub/beadhub. This is the root cause of agents accidentally creating PRs on the upstream.\n\n## Fix\nReplace the gh-pat K8s secret with a fine-grained PAT restricted to Woody88/hq-beadhub only:\n- Contents: read+write\n- Pull requests: read+write\n- Metadata: read\n\nWith this token, any attempt to push or create a PR on beadhub/beadhub will get a hard 403 from GitHub — no agent behavior, hook, or rule can bypass this.\n\n## Steps\n1. GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Fine-grained personal access tokens → Generate new token\n2. Repository access: Only select repositories → Woody88/hq-beadhub\n3. Update K8s secret: kubectl create secret generic gh-pat --from-literal=token=\u003cnew-token\u003e -n beadhub --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"beadhub-10vc","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Replace GH_TOKEN with fine-grained PAT scoped to Woody88/hq-beadhub only","updated_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
