{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"23895e15a1d978ed4ebb8069653f79572ea789be80211dfed9d09f691d37f940","created_at":"2026-03-03T07:10:00Z","created_by":"ordis","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Goal: Replace raw ADB screencap with Maestro MCP so agents can control the desktop Android emulator via natural-language MCP tool calls (screenshots, taps, text input, app launch, etc).\n\n## Background\n- The orchestrator pod already connects to the desktop emulator via ADB over TCP (192.168.2.13:5555). See docs/adb-emulator.md.\n- Screenshots currently require a multi-step workaround (emulator console port 5554 + telnet). Maestro MCP would make this a single tool call.\n\n## Tasks for neo\n\n### 1. Install Maestro CLI in agent image\n- Add Maestro install to :\n  - Install Java 17 (required by Maestro): \n  - Install Maestro: java not found.\n======================================================================================================\n Please install java on your system using your favourite package manager.\n\n Restart after installing java.\n======================================================================================================\n  - Add  to PATH\n- Rebuild and push the image (CI will handle via merge to main)\n\n### 2. Configure Maestro to use ADB-over-TCP device\n- Maestro uses ADB under the hood — once  is run, Maestro should pick up the device automatically\n- Verify:  shows the connected device\n\n### 3. Expose Maestro MCP server\n- Run  to start the MCP server (listens on stdio by default)\n- Wire it into Claude Code / orchestrator via MCP config\n\n### 4. Test screenshot via Maestro MCP\n- Confirm that a screenshot tool call through MCP returns a real (non-black) image from the desktop emulator\n\n## References\n- Install guide: https://docs.maestro.dev/maestro-cli/how-to-install-maestro-cli\n- MCP guide: https://docs.maestro.dev/get-started/maestro-mcp\n- ADB setup context: docs/adb-emulator.md (label: adb, documentation)\n","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"beadhub-mcp1","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Install Maestro CLI + MCP in agent image and configure for desktop emulator","updated_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"6aaf2afbff8a2cc4a93b7956a7d80667acbbf5d786acd3b5dd068f40663fe14d","created_at":"2026-03-03T22:46:45Z","created_by":"ordis","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"## Problem\nWhen the discord-bridge's BLPOP loop in `orchestrator-relay.ts` gets stuck (e.g. Discord API error, rate limit), messages pile up in the `orchestrator:outbox` Redis list. On bridge restart, the loop drains the entire backlog at once, flooding Discord with old messages out of order.\n\n## Root Cause\n`orchestrator-relay.ts` BLPOP loop has a 2s retry pause on error but no dead-letter handling or age-based filtering. Messages persist in the Redis list indefinitely.\n\n## Fix\n- Add a `timestamp` check: discard messages older than a configurable TTL (e.g. 5 minutes) on drain\n- On startup, log queue depth and optionally drain stale messages before entering normal BLPOP loop\n- Improve error handling in the send path so transient Discord errors don't stall the loop","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"beadhub-mz4n","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"discord-bridge: message flooding on restart from backed-up orchestrator:outbox queue","updated_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
