{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"293b38f5b714ec5dfc3488d9d31ec5fbd601f3f76b7258cb480f493a9d34d673","created_at":"2026-03-03T22:46:45Z","created_by":"ordis","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"## Problem\nWhen a `chat.message_sent` event fires, `postToOrdisChannel` in `redis-listener.ts` fetches the full message body from the BeadHub API with retries at 0ms, 500ms, and 1500ms. If all three attempts fail (API slow or race condition), it falls back to `event.preview` which is capped at ~80 chars — causing truncated messages in Discord.\n\n## Root Cause\n`redis-listener.ts` `postToOrdisChannel()` — fallback to `event.preview` on fetch failure.\n\n## Fix\n- Increase retry attempts and/or backoff window\n- If all retries fail, log a warning and skip posting rather than sending a truncated preview\n- Consider fetching by `message_id` directly rather than scanning the session message list","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"beadhub-tp4a","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"discord-bridge: cut-off messages when BeadHub API fetch falls back to event.preview","updated_at":"2026-03-04T04:43:47Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
